Here's the POC's AI running on a real Scope Classification record. We built this to test the AI capability — to prove the prompt pattern works. The platform asked the AI to analyze Vendor Risk Assessment Program and recommend how it should be scoped. The AI returned a recommendation with Low confidence — and that's a feature, not a bug. An AI that knows when it's uncertain is far more valuable than one that always sounds sure. Three things still need to happen for production-grade AI here: different models need to be tested under the hood — the platform isn't locked to one. The model needs to be grounded with institutional knowledge — your organization's policies, your prior decisions, your vocabulary. And the input itself matters — notice the control description here is high-level; richer input means more precise output. Notice the section label: AI Classification, optional. The AI assists; the Risk Manager always decides. Classification itself won't be in the production product — the rule engine takes over scope decisions. But the test of the AI capability is done.
